[2] Hospital outbreak - Uruguay
Date: Wed 22 Sep 2021
Source: Republica [in Spanish, machine trans., summ., edited]
https://www.republica.com.uy/vilardebo-ascienden-a-42-los-contagios-de-covid-tras-brote-id977601/


The coronavirus outbreak that was registered in the Vilardebó psychiatric hospital - the largest that was reported in a health center in the country in recent months - increased its number of infected and reached 42 people.

According to Telenoche, the total number of cases corresponds to 40 officials and two patients who are in the hospital of the compound.

The outbreak of cases in Vilardebó transpired last weekend. The first of the cases was detected last Thursday, when a food service official presented symptoms and tested positive after swabbing. Later, on Friday, another worker in the same sector also tested positive. Due to these cases and in accordance with the protocols, a test was carried out on all the officials in this area.

At the moment the authorities of the health establishment are waiting for the results of 800 swabs. In total, there were about 900 people who were going to be tested to rule out a possible contagion.

To alleviate the effects of the outbreak, the health center management closed the food service - where it began - until the situation is under control. The director of the hospital, Federico Sacch, indicated that he works "normally" since the positions of sick officials were filled with substitutes.

Likewise, he assured that a strict monitoring of infections is carried out. The tracking is in charge of the management team and Occupational Health of Vilardebó, as well as the health providers.

Uruguay: (Vilardeo) in-hospital outbreak, closure of food service
Vilardebo: Covid infections rise to 42 after outbreak

