[Data by country, area, or territory for 20 Sep 2021 can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/wp-content/uploads/world-pdf/2021%20WHO%20Daily%20Tables%20SEPT22_1632423740.pdf.

- The Americas region reported 45.6% of daily case numbers and 45.8% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours and maintained its position as the most severely affected region, having reported more than 88.45 million cases. The USA reported over 200 000 cases in the last 24 hours, followed by Canada (12 724). 9 additional countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, while 3 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The European region reported 30.2% of daily case numbers and 29.8% of the daily deaths reported in the past 24 hours, and total cumulative cases reported exceed 68.75 million cases. Many countries not reporting cases in the last 24 hours or longer include Belgium, Switzerland (1 case), and Kazakhstan, among others. 26 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours, and an additional 9 countries reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The Eastern Mediterranean region reported 5.6% of daily case numbers and 8.4% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 15.54 million cases. Iran reported the highest number of cases (17 397) over the last 24 hours, followed by Occupied Palestinian Territory, Iraq, Pakistan, Morocco, and Libya. Lebanon, Egypt and Jordan, reported more than 500 but fewer than 1000 cases.

- The African region reported 0.003% of daily case numbers and 0% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 5.92 million cases. Mayotte is the only country that reported any cases, while the other countries did not report cases over the last 24 hours.

- The Western Pacific region reported 10.2% of daily case numbers and 10.7% of the deaths reported in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 8.05 million cases. Philippines, reported the highest number of cases over the last 24 hours (over 16 000 cases), followed by Malaysia, Vietnam, Mongolia, Japan, South Korea, Australia, Singapore, and Cambodia.

- The South East Asia region reported 8.2% of the daily newly reported cases and 8.7% of reported deaths in the past 24 hours, having reported a cumulative total of more than 42.59 million cases. India is dominant reporting over 26 000 cases over the last 24 hours, followed by Thailand (10 919), Indonesia (3263), Myanmar (1687), Bangladesh (1562), and Nepal (1036). Sri Lanka, and Maldives have not reported any cases for the last several days.

On the Overview tab at the WHO source URL, the epidemic curve of confirmed COVID-19 cases by WHO region, 30 Dec 2019 through 22 Sep 2021, is an excellent visual representation of the pandemic. - Mod.UBA]

